<figureCitation box="[467,533,357,378]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[175,215,1570,1589]" captionTargetBox="[222,1165,184,1547]" captionTargetId="figure-57@1.[151,1171,183,1574]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1–4. Chrysobothris species, dorsal habitus. 1) C. sabae; 2) C. hispaniolae; 3) C. thoracica; 4) C. marskeae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4893208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4893208/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="84">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
; Woodley and Touroult 2012, fig. 2)...........................2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,638,303,1233]" pageId="3" pageNumber="84">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="84">
1.′ Base of pronotum with bluish green patch absent immediately anteriad scutellum, or patch only bordering posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[535,630,472,494]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[175,215,1570,1589]" captionTargetBox="[222,1165,184,1547]" captionTargetId="figure-57@1.[151,1171,183,1574]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1–4. Chrysobothris species, dorsal habitus. 1) C. sabae; 2) C. hispaniolae; 3) C. thoracica; 4) C. marskeae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4893208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4893208/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="84">Figs. 1–3</figureCitation>
)....................................................................3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
